Yes! In multiplication, we can switch the factors without changing our total.

$\begin{align}
\blueD{\text{ Number of groups}}\times\purpleC{\text{ size of the groups}} = \greenD{ \text{ total}}\\\\
\purpleC{\text{Size of the groups}}\times\blueD{\text{ number of groups}} = \greenD{ \text{ total}}
\end{align}$

We call that pattern the **commutative property of multiplication**.
